text:
2009 vintage, 651 ml bottle ( 1 pint 6 fl. oz.)

Aroma: smoke, chocolate and malt

Appearance: Dark brown with red highlights and a big fine cafe au lait head with heavy lacing;

Taste: unsweetened chocolate and burnt bitterness, a wee bit sour, and a slightly sweet aftertaste;

Palate: low carbonation, creamy texture, medium to full bodied, long creamy, slightly astringent, yeasty finish;

Overall: Big and robust.

UPDATED: DEC 18, 2009 Black in color...opaque.  Thick, creamy head.  Aroma is pretty smoky, yet not overpowering.  Slightly sweet malt flavor up front...very smooth mouthfeel.  Taste of smoke slowly blends into the back, along with a much more robust malt flavor.  Finish has somewhat of a smoke bite to it, though just enough to make you want another sip.  One of my all time favorites...this gorgeous elixir has most everything one would look for in a brew!

------ 1 Year......

Aroma - a tad subdued yet still quite smoky;
Appearance - unchanged, great lacing;
Taste - increased smokiness throughout, enhanced bitter finish;
Palate - unchanged, fantastic body;
Overall - some things only get better with time.
